The health centre is considering hiring more doctors to increase its capacity.
 Currently there are 20 doctors employed.
 Each doctor can treat 500 patients each month, so the current capacity
 is 10000 patients.
 If the number of patients exceeds the capacity in a given month, the health
 centre has to pay overtime salary which is expensive.
 The health centre has the following loss function
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
L(p,d)=\left(d+0.04\text{max}(p-500d,0)\right)^{2},
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 is the number of doctors employed, 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 is the number of patients in a month, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{max}(a,b)$
\end_inset

 is the function that returns the largest value of 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

.
 Should the health centre hire more doctors, and if so, how many, according
 to the Bayesian decision? Assume that all doctors work full-time.
 
